{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WnnsxD6PGcCqynR9abaSne","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed report.\n\n## Summary: JWT Auth Middleware & Route Registration Patterns\n\nBased on a thorough exploration of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/`, here's the complete breakdown:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Route Registration Pattern (index.ts, lines 78-302)\n\n**How routes are added:**\n\nRoutes are registered using Hono's `app.route()` and `app.use()` pattern:\n\n```typescript\n// Pattern: Middleware first, then route registration\napp.use(\"/auth/*\", createRateLimitMiddleware({...}));\napp.route(\"/auth\", createAuthRoutes({authDb, db, jwtSecret, ...}));\n\napp.use(\"/profile/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({jwtSecret, requireAllMethods: true}));\napp.route(\"/profile\", createProfileRoutes({db}));\n\napp.use(\"/coinflip/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({jwtSecret}));\napp.use(\"/coinflip/*\", createRateLimitMiddleware({...}));\napp.route(\"/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({db, connection, ...}));\n```\n\n**Key Pattern:**\n1. Middleware (`app.use()`) is applied to route path patterns\n2. Routes (`app.route()`) are mounted with a factory function that accepts dependencies\n3. Dependencies are passed through a `Props`/`Deps` interface (e.g., `ProfileRoutesDeps`)\n4. Each factory function returns a `new Hono<AppEnv>()` instance with typed context\n\n---\n\n### 2. JWT Auth Middleware (`middleware/jwt-auth.ts`)\n\n**Location:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n\n**Configuration:**\n```typescript\nexport interface JwtAuthConfig {\n  jwtSecret: Uint8Array;\n  requireAllMethods?: boolean; // Default: false (POST only)\n}\n```\n\n**What it extracts:**\n- **`userId`** from JWT `sub` (subject) claim → stored in Hono context via `c.set(\"userId\", payload.sub)`\n- **Wallet is NOT in the JWT** — routes that need wallet must resolve it from `db.getProfileByUserId(userId)`\n\n**Behavior:**\n- Verifies HS256 JWT access tokens using `jose.jwtVerify()`\n- If `requireAllMethods: false` (default): only checks POST requests, GET passes through\n- If `requireAllMethods: true`: checks all HTTP methods (used for `/profile/*`, `/referral/*`)\n- Missing/invalid Authorization header → 401 with `{ error: \"Missing or invalid Authorization header\" }`\n- Token verification failure → 401 with `{ error: \"Invalid or expired token\" }`\n\n**Context type augmentation** (`hono-env.ts`):\n```typescript\nexport type AppEnv = {\n  Variables: {\n    userId: string;\n  };\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Full Auth Pattern Example: Profile Routes\n\n**Location:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts`\n\n**Index.ts registration:**\n```typescript\n// Line 103-107\napp.use(\n  \"/profile/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret, requireAllMethods: true }),\n);\napp.route(\"/profile\", createProfileRoutes({ db }));\n```\n\n**Route factory signature:**\n```typescript\nexport interface ProfileRoutesDeps {\n  db: Db;\n}\n\nexport function createProfileRoutes(deps: ProfileRoutesDeps) {\n  const { db } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n  \n  app.get(\"/me\", async (c) => {\n    const userId = c.get(\"userId\"); // Extract from JWT\n    if (!userId) {\n      return c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n    }\n    \n    const profile = await db.getProfileByUserId(userId);\n    if (!profile) {\n      return c.json({ error: \"PROFILE_NOT_FOUND\" }, 404);\n    }\n    \n    // ... fetch and return profile data\n  });\n  \n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Example: Accessing authenticated user's wallet:**\n```typescript\nconst userId = c.get(\"userId\");\nconst profile = await db.getProfileByUserId(userId);\nconst wallet = profile.wallet; // Wallet comes from profile, not JWT\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Standard Response/Error Pattern\n\n**Success responses:**\n- Use `c.json({ ...data })` with status 200 (implicit)\n- Example from `/coinflip/create` (line 250-256):\n  ```typescript\n  return c.json({\n    transaction,\n    matchPda: matchPdaStr,\n    matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n    commitment: commitment.toString(\"hex\"),\n    lastValidBlockHeight,\n  });\n  ```\n\n**Error responses:**\n```typescript\n// 400 Bad Request\nreturn c.json({ error: \"Invalid request body\" }, 400);\n\n// Structured error for referral routes (line 49-58):\nreturn c.json({\n  error: {\n    code: \"INVALID_CODE\",\n    message: \"Code must be 3-16 characters, lowercase letters, numbers, and hyphens only\",\n  },\n}, 400);\n\n// 401 Unauthorized\nreturn c.json({ error: \"Authentication required\" }, 401);\n\n// 404 Not Found\nreturn c.json({ error: \"PROFILE_NOT_FOUND\" }, 404);\n\n// 409 Conflict\nreturn c.json({\n  error: {\n    code: \"CODE_TAKEN\",\n    message: \"This referral code is already in use\",\n    retryable: false,\n  },\n}, 409);\n\n// 429 Too Many Requests (from rate-limit middleware)\nc.header(\"Retry-After\", String(retryAfterSeconds));\nreturn c.json({ error: \"Too many requests\" }, 429);\n\n// 500 Internal Server Error\nreturn c.json({ error: \"Failed to fetch profile\" }, 500);\n```\n\n**Logging pattern:**\nAll routes include contextual logging via `logger.info/warn/error()`:\n```typescript\nlogger.info(\"coinflip create requested\", {\n  wallet: body.wallet,\n  amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n  side: body.side,\n});\n\nlogger.error(\"profile/me failed\", {\n  userId,\n  error: err instanceof Error ? err.message : \"Unknown error\",\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Complete Middleware Stack Example: Coinflip Routes\n\n**How it all stacks together** (index.ts, lines 119-145):\n```typescript\n// Apply JWT auth (POST only by default)\napp.use(\n  \"/coinflip/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: config.jwtSecret }),\n);\n\n// Apply rate limiting on top of JWT\napp.use(\n  \"/coinflip/*\",\n  createRateLimitMiddleware({\n    perWallet: config.rateLimitPerWallet,      // 10 per minute\n    global: config.rateLimitGlobal,             // 100 per minute\n    windowMs: 60_000,\n  }),\n);\n\n// Mount the routes\napp.route(\n  \"/coinflip\",\n  createCoinflipRoutes({ db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher }),\n);\n```\n\n**Execution order for a POST request:**\n1. CORS middleware (`app.use(\"*\", cors(...))`) — Line 53\n2. Request logging middleware — Line 63\n3. JWT auth middleware → extracts `userId`, stores in context\n4. Rate limit middleware → checks sliding window counters for this user\n5. Route handler (e.g., `POST /coinflip/create`) → accesses `userId` from context\n\n---\n\n### 6. Key Conventions\n\n- **BigInt serialization:** Large numbers (lamports, amounts) are converted to strings in JSON responses\n- **Wallet resolution:** Only the `userId` is in the JWT. Routes get wallet via `db.getProfileByUserId(userId)`\n- **Defense in depth:** Routes validate wallet matches authenticated user (line 94-103 in create.ts)\n- **Database transactions:** All route handlers use the same `Db` instance passed via deps\n- **Error messages:** Use both `error` (simple string) and `error: { code, message, retryable }` structures\n\n---\n\n### Files to Reference\n\n- **Index/router:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts`\n- **JWT middleware:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n- **Rate limit middleware:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/middleware/rate-limit.ts`\n- **Type definitions:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/hono-env.ts`\n- **Example routes:** \n  - Profile: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/profile.ts`\n  - Coinflip: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts`\n  - Referral: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/referral.ts`\n  - Health: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/health.ts`"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"59720d7a-048c-45e3-b4dd-63ce0cb4da31","uuid":"08553cea-9d50-4e89-a67a-dc5617d282f5","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:43:05.750Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the existing JWT auth middleware and route registration patterns in the backend. Explore:\n\n1. How routes are registered in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/index.ts` - find the pattern for adding new route groups\n2. Find the JWT auth middleware - how is it applied, what does it extract from the token (userId, wallet)?\n3. Look at an existing route that uses JWT auth (e.g. any route with auth middleware) and show me the full pattern\n4. What's the standard response/error pattern used?\n\nBe thorough - read the actual files, not just search. Focus on `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/` directory.","agentId":"a8e374abbb1f5327a","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed report.\n\n## Summary: JWT Auth Middleware & Route Registration Patterns\n\nBased on a thorough exploration of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/`, here's the complete breakdown:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Route Registration Pattern (index.ts, lines 78-302)\n\n**How routes are added:**\n\nRoutes are registered using Hono's `app.route()` and `app.use()` pattern:\n\n```typescript\n// Pattern: Middleware first, then route registration\napp.use(\"/auth/*\", createRateLimitMiddleware({...}));\napp.route(\"/auth\", createAuthRoutes({authDb, db, jwtSecret, ...}));\n\napp.use(\"/profile/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({jwtSecret, requireAllMethods: true}));\napp.route(\"/profile\", createProfileRoutes({db}));\n\napp.use(\"/coinflip/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({jwtSecret}));\napp.use(\"/coinflip/*\", createRateLimitMiddleware({...}));\napp.route(\"/coinflip\", createCoinflipRoutes({db, connection, ...}));\n```\