{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KK69n8KaMQMkhjuBrdEk9C","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed report summarizing the integration test infrastructure.\n\n## Integration Test Infrastructure Summary\n\nBased on my analysis of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`, here's how integration tests work in this backend:\n\n### **Test File Structure Overview**\n\nThe integration test file is ~1100 lines and exercises the **full create → join → settle lifecycle** using a real database and mocked Solana Connection, while exercising real HTTP endpoints.\n\n### **1. JWT Token Creation for Tests**\n\nThe test file includes a dedicated JWT helper:\n\n```typescript\n// Lines 66-78\nconst JWT_SECRET = new TextEncoder().encode(\"test-secret-for-integration-tests\");\n\nasync function makeJwt(wallet: string, userId = userIdFromWallet(wallet)) {\n  const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);\n  return new SignJWT({ wallet })\n    .setProtectedHeader({ alg: \"HS256\" })\n    .setSubject(userId)\n    .setIssuedAt(now)\n    .setExpirationTime(now + 3600)\n    .sign(JWT_SECRET);\n}\n\nfunction userIdFromWallet(wallet: string) {\n  return `usr_${wallet.slice(0, 8).toLowerCase()}`;\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Uses `jose` library's `SignJWT` to generate HS256 tokens\n- The payload includes the `wallet` address\n- The `sub` (subject) claim is a user ID derived from the wallet (format: `usr_<first8chars>`)\n- Tokens have 1-hour expiration\n- The test secret must match what the JWT middleware expects\n\n### **2. JWT Auth Middleware Pattern**\n\nThe middleware (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`) works as follows:\n\n- **Default behavior**: Only requires auth for `POST` requests\n- **Optional**: Can require auth for all methods with `requireAllMethods: true`\n- **Extraction**: Reads `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- **Verification**: Uses `jwtVerify` from `jose` to verify HS256 signature\n- **Context**: Sets `c.set(\"userId\", payload.sub)` for downstream handlers to access\n- **Response**: Returns 401 with \"Invalid or expired token\" on failure\n\n### **3. App Setup & Dependency Injection**\n\nIn `beforeEach` (lines 399-450):\n\n```typescript\n// Fresh mock Connection\nmockConn = new MockConnection();\n\n// Build the Hono app\napp = new Hono();\n\n// Add JWT middleware (only for /coinflip/*)\napp.use(\n  \"/coinflip/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: JWT_SECRET }),\n);\n\n// Mount routes with dependencies\napp.route(\n  \"/coinflip\",\n  createCoinflipRoutes({\n    db,\n    connection: mockConn as unknown as Connection,\n    serverKeypair,\n  }),\n);\n\napp.route(\"/rounds\", createRoundsRoutes({ db }));\n```\n\n**Key pattern:**\n- Routes are created as independent `Hono` apps via factory functions\n- Dependencies (db, connection, keypairs) are injected via constructor arguments\n- Middleware is applied to specific route prefixes\n- The same JWT_SECRET is used throughout tests\n\n### **4. Database Setup & Teardown**\n\n**beforeAll** (lines 302-392):\n- Creates raw postgres connection\n- Drops and recreates referral/reward tables from scratch\n- Initializes `Db` instance with migration auto-run\n- Stores both raw SQL connection and Db wrapper\n\n**beforeEach** (lines 399-403):\n- `TRUNCATE` all game/test tables with `CASCADE` and `RESTART IDENTITY`\n- Resets reward pool singleton record\n- Resets PlatformConfig cache\n\n**afterAll** (lines 394-397):\n- Closes both db and rawSql connections\n\n### **5. HTTP Request Testing Pattern**\n\nTesting a POST route with auth (lines 452-468):\n\n```typescript\nconst wallet = creatorKeypair.publicKey.toBase58();\nconst token = await makeJwt(wallet);\n\nconst createRes = await app.request(\"/coinflip/create\", {\n  method: \"POST\",\n  headers: {\n    \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n    \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${token}`,\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify(body),\n});\n\nexpect(createRes.status).toBe(200);\nconst createJson = (await createRes.json()) as { /* type */ };\n```\n\nTesting a GET route (lines 604-605):\n\n```typescript\nconst roundsRes = await app.request(`/rounds/${matchPda}`);\nexpect(roundsRes.status).toBe(200);\nconst roundsJson = (await roundsRes.json()) as Record<string, unknown>;\n```\n\n**Pattern:**\n- `app.request(path, options)` is Hono's built-in test method (no fetch needed)\n- Auth is via `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- Response has `.status` and `.json()` methods\n- JSON responses use `as Record<string, unknown>` to avoid TS errors\n\n### **6. Mock Solana Connection**\n\nCustom `MockConnection` class (lines 89-216) provides:\n\n**Core methods:**\n- `setAccount(pubkey, data, opts?)` — stores account in-memory\n- `removeAccount(pubkey)` — deletes account\n- `getAccountInfo(pubkey)` — retrieves stored account (with `rentEpoch: 0`)\n- `getProgramAccounts(programId, config?)` — filters by program owner and data comparisons\n- `getSlot()` / `slot` property — mutable to simulate chain progression\n- `sendRawTransaction(rawTx)` — captures tx, returns deterministic signature\n- `confirmTransaction()` — immediate confirmation\n- `getLatestBlockhash()` — returns static blockhash\n- `getBlockTime()` — returns current Unix timestamp\n- `getBalance()` — returns 2 SOL\n\n**Pre-populated accounts** (lines 412-430):\n- Entropy account (32 bytes with test data)\n- Coinflip config PDA (built via `buildConfigAccountData`)\n- PlatformConfig PDA (built via `buildPlatformConfigData` with fee_bps = 500 = 5%)\n\n### **7. Key Routes Under Test**\n\n**POST /coinflip/create** (with auth):\n- Requires JWT Bearer token\n- Accepts `{ wallet, amountLamports, side }`\n- Returns `{ transaction, matchPda, matchId, commitment, lastValidBlockHeight }`\n- DB stores round with phase `\"created\"`\n\n**GET /rounds/:pda** (no auth required):\n- Returns round data with camelCase keys\n- For unsettled rounds: omits `secret`, `resultHash`, `verification`\n- For settled rounds: includes all verification data including `secret`\n- Returns 404 if PDA not found\n\n### **8. Settlement Testing Pattern**\n\nThe test exercises the full settlement flow (lines 536-569):\n1. Creates a `createSettlementWorker` with poll callback\n2. Creates a `createRetrySettler` that calls `settleMatch`\n3. Calls `worker.poll()` to simulate the polling loop\n4. Awaits the settle promise to completion\n5. Verifies DB updated to phase `\"settled\"` with result data\n\n### **Files Referenced**\n\n- Test file: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n- JWT middleware: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n- Routes: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts` and `/routes/rounds.ts`"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"59720d7a-048c-45e3-b4dd-63ce0cb4da31","uuid":"b91cc5b4-9754-4ca0-9a19-a9b5a7074649","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:43:22.896Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand how integration tests work in this backend, specifically for API routes. Look at:\n\n1. `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts` - read the full file to understand the test setup (how the app is created, how requests are made, what helpers exist for auth/JWT tokens, how DB is set up/torn down)\n2. How are JWT tokens created in tests? Is there a test helper?\n3. What's the pattern for testing API routes (GET with auth)?\n\nFocus on the test infrastructure and any route-testing patterns. The file may be large - read it in chunks if needed.","agentId":"ac166c76ce1733f18","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed report summarizing the integration test infrastructure.\n\n## Integration Test Infrastructure Summary\n\nBased on my analysis of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`, here's how integration tests work in this backend:\n\n### **Test File Structure Overview**\n\nThe integration test file is ~1100 lines and exercises the **full create → join → settle lifecycle** using a real database and mocked Solana Connection, while exercising real HTTP endpoints.\n\n### **1. JWT Token Creation for Tests**\n\nThe test file includes a dedicated JWT helper:\n\n```typescript\n// Lines 66-78\nconst JWT_SECRET = new TextEncoder().encode(\"test-secret-for-integration-tests\");\n\nasync function makeJwt(wallet: string, userId = userIdFromWallet(wallet)) {\n  const now = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000);\n  return new SignJWT({ wallet })\n    .setProtectedHeader({ alg: \"HS256\" })\n    .setSubject(userId)\n    .setIssuedAt(now)\n    .setExpirationTime(now + 3600)\n    .sign(JWT_SECRET);\n}\n\nfunction userIdFromWallet(wallet: string) {\n  return `usr_${wallet.slice(0, 8).toLowerCase()}`;\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Uses `jose` library's `SignJWT` to generate HS256 tokens\n- The payload includes the `wallet` address\n- The `sub` (subject) claim is a user ID derived from the wallet (format: `usr_<first8chars>`)\n- Tokens have 1-hour expiration\n- The test secret must match what the JWT middleware expects\n\n### **2. JWT Auth Middleware Pattern**\n\nThe middleware (`/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`) works as follows:\n\n- **Default behavior**: Only requires auth for `POST` requests\n- **Optional**: Can require auth for all methods with `requireAllMethods: true`\n- **Extraction**: Reads `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- **Verification**: Uses `jwtVerify` from `jose` to verify HS256 signature\n- **Context**: Sets `c.set(\"userId\", payload.sub)` for downstream handlers to access\n- **Response**: Returns 401 with \"Invalid or expired token\" on failure\n\n### **3. App Setup & Dependency Injection**\n\nIn `beforeEach` (lines 399-450):\n\n```typescript\n// Fresh mock Connection\nmockConn = new MockConnection();\n\n// Build the Hono app\napp = new Hono();\n\n// Add JWT middleware (only for /coinflip/*)\napp.use(\n  \"/coinflip/*\",\n  createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret: JWT_SECRET }),\n);\n\n// Mount routes with dependencies\napp.route(\n  \"/coinflip\",\n  createCoinflipRoutes({\n    db,\n    connection: mockConn as unknown as Connection,\n    serverKeypair,\n  }),\n);\n\napp.route(\"/rounds\", createRoundsRoutes({ db }));\n```\n\n**Key pattern:**\n- Routes are created as independent `Hono` apps via factory functions\n- Dependencies (db, connection, keypairs) are injected via constructor arguments\n- Middleware is applied to specific route prefixes\n- The same JWT_SECRET is used throughout tests\n\n### **4. Database Setup & Teardown**\n\n**beforeAll** (lines 302-392):\n- Creates raw postgres connection\n- Drops and recreates referral/reward tables from scratch\n- Initializes `Db` instance with migration auto-run\n- Stores both raw SQL connection and Db wrapper\n\n**beforeEach** (lines 399-403):\n- `TRUNCATE` all game/test tables with `CASCADE` and `RESTART IDENTITY`\n- Resets reward pool singleton record\n- Resets PlatformConfig cache\n\n**afterAll** (lines 394-397):\n- Closes both db and rawSql connections\n\n### **5. HTTP Request Testing Pattern**\n\nTesting a POST route with auth (lines 452-468):\n\n```typescript\nconst wallet = creatorKeypair.publicKey.toBase58();\nconst token = await makeJwt(wallet);\n\nconst createRes = await app.request(\"/coinflip/create\", {\n  method: \"POST\",\n  headers: {\n    \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\",\n    \"Authorization\": `Bearer ${token}`,\n  },\n  body: JSON.stringify(body),\n});\n\nexpect(createRes.status).toBe(200);\nconst createJson = (await createRes.json()) as { /* type */ };\n```\n\nTesting a GET route (lines 604-605):\n\n```typescript\nconst roundsRes = await app.request(`/rounds/${matchPda}`);\nexpect(roundsRes.status).toBe(200);\nconst roundsJson = (await roundsRes.json()) as Record<string, unknown>;\n```\n\n**Pattern:**\n- `app.request(path, options)` is Hono's built-in test method (no fetch needed)\n- Auth is via `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- Response has `.status` and `.json()` methods\n- JSON responses use `as Record<string, unknown>` to avoid TS errors\n\n### **6. Mock Solana Connection**\n\nCustom `MockConnection` class (lines 89-216) provides:\n\n**Core methods:**\n- `setAccount(pubkey, data, opts?)` — stores account in-memory\n- `removeAccount(pubkey)` — deletes account\n- `getAccountInfo(pubkey)` — retrieves stored account (with `rentEpoch: 0`)\n- `getProgramAccounts(programId, config?)` — filters by program owner and data comparisons\n- `getSlot()` / `slot` property — mutable to simulate chain progression\n- `sendRawTransaction(rawTx)` — captures tx, returns deterministic signature\n- `confirmTransaction()` — immediate confirmation\n- `getLatestBlockhash()` — returns static blockhash\n- `getBlockTime()` — returns current Unix timestamp\n- `getBalance()` — returns 2 SOL\n\n**Pre-populated accounts** (lines 412-430):\n- Entropy account (32 bytes with test data)\n- Coinflip config PDA (built via `buildConfigAccountData`)\n- PlatformConfig PDA (built via `buildPlatformConfigData` with fee_bps = 500 = 5%)\n\n### **7. Key Routes Under Test**\n\n**POST /coinflip/create** (with auth):\n- Requires JWT Bearer token\n- Accepts `{ wallet, amountLamports, side }`\n- Returns `{ transaction, matchPda, matchId, commitment, lastValidBlockHeight }`\n- DB stores round with phase `\"created\"`\n\n**GET /rounds/:pda** (no auth required):\n- Returns round data with camelCase keys\n- For unsettled rounds: omits `secret`, `resultHash`, `verification`\n- For settled rounds: includes all verification data including `secret`\n- Returns 404 if PDA not found\n\n### **8. Settlement Testing Pattern**\n\nThe test exercises the full settlement flow (lines 536-569):\n1. Creates a `createSettlementWorker` with poll callback\n2. Creates a `createRetrySettler` that calls `settleMatch`\n3. Calls `worker.poll()` to simulate the polling loop\n4. Awaits the settle promise to completion\n5. Verifies DB updated to phase `\"settled\"` with result data\n\n### **Files Referenced**\n\n- Test file: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/__tests__/integration.test.ts`\n- JWT middleware: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`\n- Routes: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/services/backend/src/routes/create.ts` and `/routes/rounds.ts`"}],"totalDurationMs":47944,"totalTokens":50795,"totalToolUseCount":14,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":712,"cache_read_input_tokens":48159,"output_tokens":1922,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":712},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
