{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019CKoztQb2CTVdPaCux8uuS","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Specification: [400] Challenge Engine & Reward System\n2\t\n3\t## Meta\n4\t\n5\t| Field | Value |\n6\t|-------|-------|\n7\t| Status | Ready |\n8\t| Priority | P1 |\n9\t| Track | Core |\n10\t| NR_OF_TRIES | 10 |\n11\t\n12\t---\n13\t\n14\t## Overview\n15\t\n16\tA backend service that gives players daily and weekly gameplay objectives, tracks progress automatically via game settlement events, awards points for wagering, drops loot crates with configurable probability, and runs scheduled Dogpile events with boosted multipliers. Every challenge drives lobby activity — no social media chores, no off-platform actions.\n17\t\n18\tThe system introduces three new primitives:\n19\t1. **Points** — earned passively per $ wagered (configurable rate). Pre-TGE allocation signal. Free to mint.\n20\t2. **Loot Crates** — random drops after settled games. Two types: points crates (free) and SOL crates (capped by reward-pool accounting).\n21\t3. **Reward Pool** — a configurable share of collected platform fees, tracked as an accounting ledger that caps and records SOL crate payouts.\n22\t\n23\tThe challenge engine is event-driven, plugging into the existing async event queue (spec 301). It receives `game.settled` events from the settlement workers, evaluates progress against active challenges, and emits reward-intent events for downstream handlers. Challenge evaluation stays separate from reward side-effects: `game.settled` advances progress and emits `reward.pool_fund`, `points.grant`, and `crate.drop`, while dedicated handlers perform pool accounting, point grants, crate recording, and SOL payouts.\n24\t\n25\t### Design Principles (from reference spec)\n26\t\n27\t1. **Every challenge must fill a lobby or make the platform more alive.** No off-platform actions.\n28\t2. **One progression number: points.** No XP, no levels, no badges, no cosmetics.\n29\t3. **Rewards are crates and points. That's it.** No shops, no catalogs.\n30\t\n31\t## User Stories\n32\t\n33\t- As a player, I want to see daily and weekly challenges so that I have concrete goals beyond individual games\n34\t- As a player, I want my challenge progress to update automatically when I play so that I don't need to claim or submit proof\n35\t- As a player, I want to earn points proportional to my wagered volume so that every game feels rewarding\n36\t- As a player, I want a chance at loot crates after each game so that settlements have an extra moment of excitement\n37\t- As a player, I want a bonus reward for completing all my daily challenges so that I'm motivated to finish the set\n38\t- As a new player, I want guided onboarding challenges so that I learn the platform's game types and mechanics\n39\t- As a player, I want Dogpile events to boost my point earnings so that I'm motivated to play during peak hours\n40\t- As an operator, I want to configure point rates, crate drop rates, and reward pool share without redeploying so that I can tune economics live\n41\t- As an operator, I want lightweight anti-abuse signals so that obviously suspicious reward activity can be reviewed without over-engineering M1\n42\t\n43\t---\n44\t\n45\t## Capability Alignment\n46\t\n47\t- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 \"Not Implemented\" -> \"Reward loops and progression expansion\"; Section 8 Workstream A (core game reliability provides the settlement events this consumes)\n48\t- **Current baseline fit**: Not Implemented\n49\t- **Planning bucket**: Core (extends the game loop)\n50\t- **Reference doc**: `docs/references/challenge-engine-spec.md` (full design research)\n51\t\n52\t## Required Context Files\n53\t\n54\t- `docs/specs/301-async-event-queue/spec.md` — event queue we plug into\n55\t- `docs/specs/300-referral-system/spec.md` — pattern for event handlers, DB conventions\n56\t- `backend/services/backend/src/queue/` — event queue implementation\n57\t- `backend/services/backend/src/worker/settle-tx.ts` — settlement hot path (emits new events)\n58\t- `backend/services/backend/src/db.ts` — DB client and query patterns\n59\t- `backend/services/backend/migrations/007_game_entries.sql` — game_entries schema (data source for adapters)\n60\t- `docs/DESIGN_REFERENCE.md` — trust model, fee structure (500 bps)\n61\t\n62\t## Contract Files\n63\t\n64\t- No existing mocks — new system\n65\t- API contract defined in FR-14 below\n66\t- Event contracts defined in FR-1\n67\t\n68\t---\n69\t\n70\t## System Invariants\n71\t\n72\t1. **Points are free to mint.** No budget constraint. Points never come from the reward pool.\n73\t2. **Reward pool is accounting-only in M1.** All on-chain fees still settle to the single treasury; `reward_pool` is an off-chain ledger that tracks how much of that fee flow is reserved for crate economics.\n74\t3. **Reward pool balance cannot go negative.** If pool < `sol_crate_min_value`, SOL crate drops are suppressed until the pool recovers.\n75\t4. **Challenge progress is idempotent.** Processing the same `game.settled` event twice produces the same progress state.\n76\t5. **Reward side-effects are idempotent.** Pool funding, point grants, crate creation, and SOL payouts must dedupe on domain keys from the payload, never `event_queue.id`.\n77\t6. **Settlement must never block on challenge processing.** Challenge evaluation is async (via event queue). Settlement latency is unaffected.\n78\t7. **All monetary values in lamports (BIGINT).** SOL conversion only at display boundaries.\n79\t8. **Operator config changes take effect immediately.** No redeploy, no restart. Read from `reward_config` table on each evaluation.\n80\t\n81\t---\n82\t\n83\t## Functional Requirements\n84\t\n85\t### FR-1: Game Settlement Event Emission\n86\t\n87\tExtend the settlement workers to emit a `game.settled` event into the async event queue for every settled game. This is the foundation all downstream processing depends on.\n88\t\n89\t**Event payload:**\n90\t\n91\t```typescript\n92\t{\n93\t  roundId: string;          // match_id (hex)\n94\t  roundPda: string;         // on-chain PDA\n95\t  game: \"coinflip\" | \"lord\" | \"closecall\";\n96\t  players: Array<{\n97\t    userId: string;\n98\t    wallet: string;\n99\t    amountLamports: string; // bigint as string\n100\t    isWinner: boolean | null; // null = refund\n101\t    payoutLamports: string;\n102\t    isCreator: boolean;\n103\t  }>;\n104\t  feeLamports: string;\n105\t  settledAt: string;        // ISO 8601\n106\t}\n107\t```\n108\t\n109\tThe event MUST be emitted within the same DB transaction as the settlement write (same pattern as referral earnings recording).\n110\t\n111\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n112\t- [ ] `game.settled` event type added to `EventTypes` in `event-types.ts`\n113\t- [ ] `settle-tx.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for coinflip rounds\n114\t- [ ] `settle-tx.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for lord (jackpot) rounds\n115\t- [ ] `closecall-clock.ts` emits `game.settled` within the settlement transaction for closecall rounds\n116\t- [ ] Event payload matches the schema above (all fields present, amounts as string-encoded lamports)\n117\t- [ ] Existing settlement latency is not measurably affected (event is a single INSERT, no blocking)\n118\t- [ ] Duplicate settlement retries may enqueue duplicate `game.settled` rows safely because downstream handlers dedupe on domain keys, not `event_queue.id`\n119\t\n120\t---\n121\t\n122\t### FR-2: Challenge Engine Data Model\n123\t\n124\tDatabase schema for challenges, assignments, and progress tracking.\n125\t\n126\t**Tables:**\n127\t\n128\t```sql\n129\t-- Operator-tunable reward/economy parameters\n130\tCREATE TABLE reward_config (\n131\t  key         TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n132\t  value       TEXT NOT NULL,           -- JSON-encoded value\n133\t  updated_at  TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n134\t);\n135\t\n136\t-- Player point balances and lifetime stats\n137\tCREATE TABLE player_points (\n138\t  user_id             TEXT PRIMARY KEY,\n139\t  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n140\t  balance             BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,        -- current spendable\n141\t  lifetime_earned     BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,        -- monotonic, never decreases\n142\t  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n143\t);\n144\t\n145\t-- Immutable point grant ledger (source of truth for history + idempotency)\n146\tCREATE TABLE point_grants (\n147\t  id                  BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n148\t  user_id             TEXT NOT NULL,\n149\t  wallet              TEXT NOT NULL,\n150\t  source_type         TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (source_type IN ('wager', 'challenge_completed', 'bonus_completed', 'crate_points')),\n151\t  source_id           TEXT NOT NULL,                    -- round_id, assignment_id, bonus_completion_id, crate_drop_id\n152\t  amount              BIGINT NOT NULL,\n153\t  metadata            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n154\t  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n155\t  UNIQUE (user_id, source_type, source_id)\n156\t);\n157\t\n158\tCREATE INDEX idx_point_grants_user_created ON point_grants (user_id, created_at DESC);\n159\t\n160\t-- Reward pool accounting (single row, updated atomically)\n161\tCREATE TABLE reward_pool (\n162\t  id                  INT PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT 1 CHECK (id = 1),  -- singleton, accounting-only ledger\n163\t  balance_lamports    BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n164\t  lifetime_funded     BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,    -- total fees -> pool\n165\t  lifetime_paid       BIGINT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,    -- total crate payouts\n166\t  updated_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n167\t);\n168\t\n169\t-- Append-only pool funding ledger for idempotent reward_pool_fund handling\n170\tCREATE TABLE reward_pool_fundings (\n171\t  id                  BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n172\t  round_id            TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,         -- one funding record per settled round\n173\t  fee_lamports        BIGINT NOT NULL,\n174\t  funded_lamports     BIGINT NOT NULL,\n175\t  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n176\t);\n177\t\n178\t-- Campaign container (Daily, Weekly, Onboarding, Dogpile)\n179\tCREATE TABLE campaigns (\n180\t  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n181\t  name            TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,\n182\t  campaign_type   TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (campaign_type IN ('daily', 'weekly', 'onboarding', 'dogpile')),\n183\t  starts_at       TIMESTAMPTZ,                  -- NULL = always active\n184\t  ends_at         TIMESTAMPTZ,                  -- NULL = no end\n185\t  is_active       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true,\n186\t  config          JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',  -- type-specific config (e.g., dogpile multiplier)\n187\t  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n188\t);\n189\t\n190\t-- Challenge template definitions (data, not code)\n191\tCREATE TABLE challenges (\n192\t  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n193\t  campaign_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES campaigns(id),\n194\t  title           TEXT NOT NULL,\n195\t  description     TEXT,\n196\t  action          TEXT NOT NULL,                 -- M1 adapter type: game_won, game_completed, lobby_filled\n197\t  scope           TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'any' CHECK (scope IN ('any', 'coinflip', 'lord', 'closecall')),\n198\t  condition       TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'count', -- M1: count, unique_game_types\n199\t  threshold       INT NOT NULL,                  -- target value\n200\t  reward_type     TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (reward_type IN ('points', 'crate')),\n201\t  reward_amount   INT,                           -- points amount (if reward_type = points)\n202\t  prerequisite_id BIGINT REFERENCES challenges(id),  -- for chains (onboarding)\n203\t  eligible_if     JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',   -- M1: unused. M2+: eligibility rules (e.g., {\"min_games_played\": 10})\n204\t  sort_order      INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,        -- display ordering within campaign\n205\t  is_active       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true,\n206\t  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n207\t);\n208\t\n209\t-- Per-player challenge assignments for a specific period\n210\tCREATE TABLE challenge_assignments (\n211\t  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n212\t  user_id         TEXT NOT NULL,\n213\t  challenge_id    BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES challenges(id),\n214\t  period_key      TEXT NOT NULL,                 -- e.g., \"daily:2026-04-03\", \"weekly:2026-W14\", \"onboarding\"\n215\t  status          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'active' CHECK (status IN ('active', 'completed', 'expired')),\n216\t  progress        INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,\n217\t  target          INT NOT NULL,                  -- copied from challenge.threshold at assignment time\n218\t  assigned_at     TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n219\t  expires_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,                   -- NULL for one_time (onboarding)\n220\t  completed_at    TIMESTAMPTZ,\n221\t  UNIQUE (user_id, challenge_id, period_key)\n222\t);\n223\t\n224\tCREATE INDEX idx_assignments_active ON challenge_assignments (user_id, status) WHERE status = 'active';\n225\tCREATE INDEX idx_assignments_period ON challenge_assignments (period_key, status);\n226\t\n227\t-- Tracks which game sessions contributed to progress (for anti-gaming audit + idempotency)\n228\tCREATE TABLE progress_events (\n229\t  id                  BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n230\t  assignment_id       BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES challenge_assignments(id),\n231\t  round_id            TEXT NOT NULL,             -- match_id from game.settled event\n232\t  user_id             TEXT NOT NULL,\n233\t  progress_delta      INT NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,    -- how much this event advanced progress\n234\t  metadata            JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}', -- adapter context (e.g., {\"game\":\"coinflip\"} for unique_game_types)\n235\t  created_at          TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n236\t  UNIQUE (assignment_id, round_id)               -- idempotency: same round can't count twice\n237\t);\n238\t\n239\t-- Completion bonus definitions (meta-quest: complete all dailies -> bonus)\n240\tCREATE TABLE completion_bonuses (\n241\t  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n242\t  campaign_id     BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES campaigns(id),\n243\t  title           TEXT NOT NULL,\n244\t  description     TEXT,\n245\t  required_count  INT NOT NULL,                  -- how many challenges must be completed\n246\t  reward_type     TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (reward_type IN ('points', 'crate')),\n247\t  reward_amount   INT,                           -- points amount (if reward_type = points)\n248\t  is_active       BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT true,\n249\t  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n250\t);\n251\t\n252\t-- Tracks bonus completion per player per period\n253\tCREATE TABLE bonus_completions (\n254\t  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n255\t  user_id         TEXT NOT NULL,\n256\t  bonus_id        BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES completion_bonuses(id),\n257\t  period_key      TEXT NOT NULL,\n258\t  completed_at    TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n259\t  UNIQUE (user_id, bonus_id, period_key)\n260\t);\n261\t\n262\t-- Loot crate drops\n263\tCREATE TABLE crate_drops (\n264\t  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n265\t  user_id         TEXT NOT NULL,\n266\t  trigger_type    TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (trigger_type IN ('game_settled', 'challenge_completed', 'bonus_completed')),\n267\t  trigger_id      TEXT NOT NULL,                 -- round_id, assignment_id, or bonus_completion_id\n268\t  crate_type      TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (crate_type IN ('points', 'sol')),\n269\t  contents_amount TEXT NOT NULL,                 -- lamports (sol) or points amount, as string\n270\t  status          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending' CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'granted', 'failed')),\n271\t  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n272\t  granted_at      TIMESTAMPTZ,\n273\t  UNIQUE (user_id, trigger_type, trigger_id)\n274\t);\n275\t\n276\tCREATE INDEX idx_crate_drops_user ON crate_drops (user_id, created_at DESC);\n277\tCREATE INDEX idx_crate_drops_pending ON crate_drops (status) WHERE status = 'pending';\n278\t\n279\t-- Fraud flags\n280\tCREATE TABLE fraud_flags (\n281\t  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n282\t  user_id         TEXT NOT NULL,\n283\t  flag_type       TEXT NOT NULL,                 -- velocity, repeated_opponent, etc.\n284\t  details         JSONB NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}',\n285\t  related_id      TEXT,                          -- crate_drop id, assignment id, etc.\n286\t  status          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'open' CHECK (status IN ('open', 'reviewed', 'dismissed')),\n287\t  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),\n288\t  resolved_at     TIMESTAMPTZ\n289\t);\n290\t\n291\t-- Dogpile event schedule and state\n292\tCREATE TABLE dogpile_events (\n293\t  id              BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY PRIMARY KEY,\n294\t  campaign_id     BIGINT REFERENCES campaigns(id),\n295\t  starts_at       TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,\n296\t  ends_at         TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,\n297\t  multiplier      NUMERIC(4,2) NOT NULL DEFAULT 2.0,\n298\t  status          TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'scheduled' CHECK (status IN ('scheduled', 'active', 'ended', 'cancelled')),\n299\t  created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()\n300\t);\n301\t\n302\tCREATE INDEX idx_dogpile_active ON dogpile_events (status, starts_at, ends_at) WHERE status IN ('scheduled', 'active');\n303\t```\n304\t\n305\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n306\t- [ ] Migration file `0XX_challenge_engine.sql` creates all tables above\n307\t- [ ] All tables follow project conventions: BIGINT IDENTITY, CHECK constraints on TEXT enums, TIMESTAMPTZ, snake_case\n308\t- [ ] `reward_config` seeded with default values on migration (see FR-13)\n309\t- [ ] `reward_pool` seeded with single row (balance 0)\n310\t- [ ] `reward_pool_fundings` provides idempotent, append-only pool funding records keyed by `round_id`\n311\t- [ ] `point_grants` provides ledger-grade history for every points award path\n312\t- [ ] Foreign key constraints enforced (challenges -> campaigns, assignments -> challenges, etc.)\n313\t- [ ] Unique constraints prevent duplicate assignments, duplicate progress events, duplicate bonus completions, duplicate point grants, and duplicate crate drops\n314\t- [ ] Indexes support the hot queries: active assignments by user, points history by user, pending crate drops, active dogpile events\n315\t\n316\t---\n317\t\n318\t### FR-3: Points Earning System\n319\t\n320\tPlayers earn points proportional to their wagered volume on settled games. Points are free to mint (no budget constraint). Wager points are not applied inline in the `game.settled` handler; instead, eligible player processing emits a `points.grant` event and the dedicated handler writes an immutable `point_grants` ledger row before updating aggregates.\n321\t\n322\t**Formula:**\n323\t```\n324\tbase_points = floor(wager_usd * points_per_dollar)\n325\tmultiplier  = is_dogpile_active ? dogpile_multiplier : 1.0\n326\tearned      = floor(base_points * multiplier)\n327\t```\n328\t\n329\tWhere `wager_usd = amount_lamports * sol_price_usd / 1e9`. SOL/USD price is fetched from the existing `/price/sol-usd` endpoint (already used by Close Call).\n330\t\n331\tPoints are awarded to ALL players in a settled game (winners and losers), because points reward engagement, not outcomes.\n332\t\n333\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n334\t- [ ] Eligible settled-game processing emits one `points.grant` event per eligible player with a domain key derived from `(user_id, round_id, source_type='wager')`\n335\t- [ ] `points.grant` handler calculates points for each player using `points_per_dollar` from `reward_config`\n336\t- [ ] SOL/USD conversion uses the existing price service (cached, not per-event RPC)\n337\t- [ ] Points awarded to both winners and losers in a settled game\n338\t- [ ] Dogpile multiplier applied when a `dogpile_events` row is active at `settledAt` time\n339\t- [ ] `point_grants` row inserted before `player_points.balance` and `lifetime_earned` are incremented atomically\n340\t- [ ] `player_points` row created on first earn (upsert pattern)\n341\t- [ ] Points calculation is deterministic and idempotent via `point_grants UNIQUE (user_id, source_type, source_id)`, not `progress_events`\n342\t\n343\t---\n344\t\n345\t### FR-4: Reward Pool & SOL Crate Economics\n346\t\n347\tA configurable share of platform fees funds the reward pool. The reward pool is accounting-only in M1: all on-chain fees still land in the single treasury, and the challenge system records an off-chain allocation ledger used to cap SOL crate economics. No second wallet movement or second on-chain fee transfer happens during settlement.\n348\t\n349\t**Fee flow:**\n350\t```\n351\tGame settles -> 5% fee (500 bps) -> treasury\n352\t                                  \\-> reward_pool_fee_share (e.g., 20%) -> reward_pool\n353\t```\n354\t\n355\tImplementation: settled-round processing emits a `reward.pool_fund` event once per round. The handler first inserts `reward_pool_fundings(round_id, fee_lamports, funded_lamports)` as its idempotency guard, then atomically increments `reward_pool.balance_lamports` and `reward_pool.lifetime_funded`.\n356\t\n357\t**SOL crate payout:**\n358\t```\n359\tpayout = floor(reward_pool.balance_lamports * sol_crate_pool_pct)\n360\t```\n361\t\n362\tIf `payout < sol_crate_min_value` (config), the SOL crate is suppressed (not dropped). Player doesn't know they \"missed\" it — the roll simply doesn't happen when the pool is too low.\n363\t\n364\tAfter payout: `reward_pool.balance_lamports -= payout`, `reward_pool.lifetime_paid += payout`. The `crate.drop` handler MUST acquire a row lock (`SELECT ... FOR UPDATE`) on the `reward_pool` singleton before reading balance, to prevent concurrent crate handlers from double-spending the same balance. Operationally, actual SOL still comes from the treasury-managed payout wallet; `reward_pool` is the accounting cap and audit trail.\n365\t\n366\t**Acceptance Criteria:**\n367\t- [ ] Settled-round processing emits one `reward.pool_fund` event per round\n368\t- [ ] `reward.pool_fund` handler calculates `floor(feeLamports * reward_pool_fee_share)` from config\n369\t- [ ] `reward.pool_fund` handler dedupes on `round_id` via `reward_pool_fundings` before mutating `reward_pool`\n370\t- [ ] `reward_pool.balance_lamports` incremented atomically within the handler's transaction\n371\t- [ ] SOL crate payout calculated as `floor(balance * sol_crate_pool_pct)`\n372\t- [ ] SOL crate suppressed (not created) when calculated payout < `sol_crate_min_value`\n373\t- [ ] Reward pool remains accounting-only: no second on-chain fee split, no separate settlement-time wallet transfer\n374\t- [ ] Pool balance never goes negative (payout subtracted only after validation)\n375\t- [ ] `reward_pool.lifetime_funded` and `lifetime_paid` updated for audit/analytics\n376\t- [ ] All pool operations happen within a serializable or row-locked transaction (no race conditions on balance)\n377\t\n378\t---\n379\t\n380\t### FR-5: Loot Crate Drops\n381\t\n382\tAfter each settled game, each eligible player has a random chance of receiving a loot crate. Two types: points crate (free) and SOL crate (pool-funded by the accounting-only reward pool).\n383\t\n384\t**Drop logic (per player per settled game):**\n385\t```\n386\troll = random()\n387\tif roll < sol_crate_drop_rate AND pool can fund:\n388\t    drop SOL crate (payout = floor(pool.balance * sol_crate_pool_pct))\n389\telif roll < sol_crate_drop_rate + points_crate_drop_rate:\n390\t    drop points crate (amount = random in [points_crate_min, points_crate_max])\n391\telse:\n392\t    no drop\n393\t```\n394\t\n395\tSOL crate is checked first (higher value, lower probability). If pool can't fund it, the roll is wasted (no fallback to points crate — keeps the economics clean).\n396\t\n397\tCrate drops are recorded in `crate_drops` table by a dedicated `crate.drop` handler. SOL crate grants are processed via a new event (`crate.sol_payout`) through the async queue, following the same pattern as `referral.claim_requested` — the handler sends SOL from the treasury-managed payout wallet to the player's wallet.\n398\t\n399\tPoints crate grants do not mutate balances inline. The `crate.drop` handler records the crate, then emits `points.grant` with `source_type = 'crate_points'`.\n400\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01JdQuGjXRPpkWLbNTnG6YkG","session_id":"59720d7a-048c-45e3-b4dd-63ce0cb4da31","uuid":"7819269a-2ae5-4cdd-919e-8fee61d76134","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:43:54.830Z"}
